summary.title: Practical Exercise 1 - Threat Modeling
summary.description: A MongoDB database will pre-register student voters and authenticate their eligibility. A web app built with HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, and Handlebars will enable authentication and voting. A Node.js server with a RESTful API will handle login and voting status, while Web3.js will interact with an Ethereum node to process transactions via smart contracts. The transaction status will be relayed back to the server and displayed on the web app.
